My main loop looks like this now:
```c
int cc = 0;
while (!glfwWindowShouldClose(mWindow))
{
    // my updates and drawing here
    // ...

    glfwSwapBuffers(mWindow);
    glfwPollEvents();
    logD("POLL EVENTS %d", cc++);
}
```
the line "POLL EVENTS" increment counter permanently (when i press Ctrl+V in Gedit)
do I need to call something else?

p.s. logD is a printf analog
